<TITLE> Dipu Moni warns of 'AL infiltration' ahead of war crimes trials </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chandpur, Mar 27 (bdnews24.com)  Foreign minister Dipu Moni warned pary supporters on Saturday that "war criminals", intent on jeopardising upcoming war crimes trials, might infiltrate into Awami League during its current drive to boost party membership. "It's natural that we will face impediment at every step of holding the trials. War criminals might create hurdles by entering into the party during the ongoing recruitment campaign," Dipu Moni, elected from Chandpur, said while launching a party recruitment drive in the district town. The government last week named a three-member tribunal, seven-member investigation agency and 12-member panel of prosecutors to hold the trial of those accused of committing war crimes in 1971. Moni asked local leaders and activists to be alert so that no militant, terrorist or anti-liberation force can enrol into the party. "We'll have to be careful while recruiting new members," she said. The ruling party recently launched a month long countrywide 'mass communication' tour aimed at sharing views with AL supporters, boosting grassroots strength and recruiting new members. The minister said that the younger generation and women had a major contribution in the national elections to vote Awami League to power. They should be given preference during the recruitment process, she
